      "date": "2020-08-24 23:28:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2\n\n> This is going to break many other patches :-(\n\nDo you think?  While Gerrit reports many \"conflicts\", those are only at the file level, it does not actually check if there are conflicts at the line level.  I think with only 2 lines of context per patch there is a relatively low chance of this conflicting with another patch during any landing cycle.",
